# Architecture-First Development

Before implementing any new feature, **always read and consult**:

```
travel-and-tour-saas-app/docs/architecture.md
```

## Why

This document defines the canonical patterns, conventions, and architectural decisions for the codebase. All new features must align with what is already established there — including layer boundaries, data flow, naming conventions, module structure, and integration points.

## How to Apply

1. Read `architecture.md` before writing any new code for a feature
2. Identify which layers, modules, or services the feature touches
3. Follow the patterns already defined for those areas — do not introduce new patterns unless explicitly asked
4. If a pattern doesn't exist yet for the use case, flag it and propose an addition to `architecture.md` consistent with the existing style
